title.narrative: SUR 2.1 SYSTEM STRENGTHENING IN Early Child Development (ECD)

description.narrative: Strengthened national frameworks, policies, plans and standards to increase access to high-quality, equitable, inclusive, and holistic early childhood development, learning and care environments for girls and boys (0-8 years) and their families by 2021, including in emergencies, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Child Health, Early Learning, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health And Emergencies, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Wash In Schools And Ecd Centres. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, all children and adolescents, especially the most disadvantaged among them, have improved their education and developmental outcomes and accessed equitable and inclusive learning environments across the life cycle, including in emergencies.
